	<div id="p91" class="post bg1">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p91"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=91&amp;sid=6e7acff56ddaaca4c3f8158d89a93dd7#p91"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=60&amp;sid=6e7acff56ddaaca4c3f8158d89a93dd7" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">nikescar</a></strong> &raquo; 30 Mar 2011, 09:09 </p>

			

			<div class="content"><p>I'll start with these:</p><br /><p>1. Would making the screen manager work the same way as the camera manager make sense? I like how you can just call up the cam.name to assign the camera yor own unique name if you don't want to use the default. Also it might be useful to have a method, like the camera manager's SetActiveCamera, called SetActiveScreen for setting the current screen.</p><br /><p>2. I'm not sure what it would take but, a better explanation of the SimpleConcreteKeyboardInputPlayable, BindKeyCommand and CommandProcessor would be great. I understand about half of what's going on.</p><br /><p>3. How exactly should the engine components be used? InputAdvanced and MessageDeliver are in nearly every screen but what are the capapbilties and uses? Also, when should you add, remove or reuse?</p><br /><p>4. Is it possible to remove just some of the Drawing.Draw2dTextAt2dLocation text or can you only get rid of it all using ClearAll()? There may be times where I want to delete only some of the text on the screen but keep the rest. Also an example of dynamic text (where text change like in a fps counter) would be helpful. If dynamic text is done in Update() then disregard this last part.</p><br /><p>5. BrutalForceWorld is used for most of the screens. What should be used for a title screen or menu screen where there is no use for physics or 3D?</p><br /><p>6. (This one is a matter of preference) With the post effects in the engine, would it make more sense to title them PostEffectToon instead of ToonPostEffect? This way when you're looking for effects to apply you don't need to remember what they are called, intellisense will show them as soon as you type PostEffect. There may be other areas where this same approach could be taken.</p><br /><p>7. Is it feasible to have a command in CleanUp that will automatically remove anything created in the screen? Something like screen.RemoveAllOnExit(true). Each screen would have to keep track of what was added. It seems like needing to remove everything would be a likely occurance.</p><br /><p>8. Could we get a list of components (or component types) that should be removed from screens on closing? I'm not sure which are persistant and which die when the screen closes.<br /></p><br /></div>

			

		</div>

		
			<dl class="postprofile" id="profile91">
