			<h3 ><a href="#p95"></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=95&amp;sid=6e7acff56ddaaca4c3f8158d89a93dd7#p95"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=59&amp;sid=6e7acff56ddaaca4c3f8158d89a93dd7">DustinHorne</a></strong> &raquo; 30 Mar 2011, 16:50 </p>

			

			<div class="content"><p>A note on Bruno's post, I think the scene definition file would be great.  One thing that might work better though is to use a binary format to make it more compact.  The planned world editor could generate and read XML, but could produce a final binary file for use.  These things will be important for maximizing efficiency on the xBox since project size is limited to 150 MB for AppHub.<br /></p><br /></div>

			

		</div>

		
